# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.lifecycle
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Document the lifecycle of kernel builds, deployments, and cluster
#   maintenance. This file defines the long-term operational flow for the
#   k3s cluster.
#
# Lifecycle Stages:
#
#   1. Build Stage (builder user)
#        - Prepare kernel tree
#        - Run distributed build
#        - Validate artifacts
#
#   2. Backup Stage (ansible user)
#        - Run kernel-backup.yml
#
#   3. Deployment Stage
#        - Run deploy-kernel.yml
#
#   4. Verification Stage
#        - Run verification pipeline
#
#   5. Monitoring Stage
#        - Run cluster-health.yml
#        - Run cluster-service-report.yml
#
#   6. Rollback Stage (if needed)
#        - Run kernel-rollback.yml
#
# Notes:
#   - This file defines the authoritative lifecycle for cluster operations.
#   - Ensures consistency, safety, and reproducibility.
# =============================================================================
